We set the two equations equal to each other and solve for $x$: \begin{align*}
2.35+0.25x&=1.75+0.40x\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 0.15x&=0.60\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=4
\end{align*}Now we can plug $x=4$ into either equation to find the price of beef: \begin{align*}
b&=2.35+0.25(4)\\
&=\boxed{3.35}
\end{align*}Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{\$3.35}$.
